Class TemporalGraphCollectionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.TemporalGraphCollectionFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class TemporalGraphCollectionFactory
extends Object
implements BaseGraphCollectionFactory<TemporalGraphHead,TemporalVertex,TemporalEdge,TemporalGraph,TemporalGraphCollection>
    Responsible for creating instances of TemporalGraphCollection based on a specific layout.

      • fromNonTemporalDataSets

        public <G extends GraphHead,V extends Vertex,E extends Edge> TemporalGraphCollection fromNonTemporalDataSets(org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<G> graphHead,
                                                                                                             TimeIntervalExtractor<G> graphHeadTimeIntervalExtractor,
                                                                                                             org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<V> vertices,
                                                                                                             TimeIntervalExtractor<V> vertexTimeIntervalExtractor,
                                                                                                             org.apache.flink.api.java.DataSet<E> edges,
                                                                                                             TimeIntervalExtractor<E> edgeTimeIntervalExtractor)
        Creates a TemporalGraphCollection instance. By the provided timestamp extractors, it is possible to extract temporal information from the data to define a timestamp or time interval that represents the beginning and end of the element's validity (valid time).
        Type Parameters:
        G - The graph head type.
        V - The vertex type.
        E - The edge type.
        Parameters:
        graphHead - graph head DataSet
        graphHeadTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from graph heads
        vertices - vertex DataSet
        vertexTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from vertices
        edges - edge DataSet
        edgeTimeIntervalExtractor - extractor to pick the time interval from edges
        Returns:
        the logical graph represented as temporal graph with defined valid times

        Creates a TemporalGraphCollection from a (non-temporal) base graph collection. This method calls fromNonTemporalDataSets(DataSet, DataSet, DataSet) on the graph collections element data sets.
        Parameters:
        collection - Some base graph collection.
        Returns:
        The resulting temporal graph collection.
